Indeed, as we assumed at the stage of the spectra’s preliminary analysis, CDs FL sensitivity to concentrations of different cations influence the quality of the inverse problem solution dramatically. Thus, RMSE of Ni2+ cation concentration determination is the largest among studied cations (Fig. 5
                        ). We assume that the similar RMSE ratio for three cations will remain in other approaches. Note that the error in determining the concentration of the NO3
                        – anion is several times higher than the corresponding values for cations. We assume that this is due to the negatively charged surface of the CDs (see Table 1), which prevents the localization of anions near CDs.
